post_text: Friday is the 2019 Elementary Play sponsored by MHS-PTO. For all you parents who are wondering what kind of activities is planned here ya go.... We will start by having annual races & survivor game in the gym, we will break for lunch, then weather permitting we will go outside for afternoon full of activities. If it’s still to wet to go outside we will set up activities in the multipurpose room. Your child can purchase meal armbands as well as game/concession tickets throughout the whole day. Tickets are .25 per ticket. And of course Kona Ice will be there as well. They have $3,$4,$5 specials and $3 refills on $5 cup. Let’s hope this rain goes away so we can go outside and have some fun in the sun on Friday. Hope to see you all there!!! #pantherpride

post_text:
The Meadow Heights PTO would like to take a minute to recognize all of the amazing teachers we have at Meadow Heights. They spend countless hours with our children and strive to see them each succeed. The least we can do is show them a week full of extra appreciation each year. This is a copy of the flyer that was sent to each teacher to get them excited for this week. Our PTO members are awesome and donate items to help fund all the daily goodies as well as spend time making each day special. Not only do they get these special “thank you” we surprise them each day with a small gift and saying each day in their mailbox.
So make sure if you see your local teachers this week to give them an extra thank you for all the hard work they do! #pantherpride

post_text: Saturday we had our Annual Easter Egg Hunt. We changed a few things this year and incorporated some arts and crafts in as well. We ended up having to “hunt” eggs indoors due to the mud, but that didn’t stop all the awesome kids who still came Everyone got goodies and treats to take home. Hope you all had a good time and can’t wait till next year!

post_text: On Tuesday 3/20 6 of our PTO members were able to attend PTO Today Live Convention in St Charles. As you can see lots of smiles, laughs, and good times had by all. We even had 2 members win some awesome goodies. We were able to get lots of information on different fundraisers out there and how to use resources to help build our PTO program.
